apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: pod
spec:
  containers:
  - name: main
    image: alpine
    command: ["/bin/sleep", "999999"]
    securityContext:
      readOnlyRootFilesystem: true
  dnsPolicy: ClusterFirst
  restartPolicy: AlwaysapiVersion: v1

kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: pod
spec:
  containers:
  - name: main
    image: alpine
    command: ["/bin/sleep", "999999"]
    livenessProbe:
      exec:
        command:
        - cat
        - /tmp/healthy
      initialDelaySeconds: 5
      periodSeconds: 5

Enforcing a read-only root filesystem can make containers more secure.

mv /root/apps/app1-510d6362.yaml /root/insecure

